	The Address is all you need	I'm writing this review from my comfy bed at the Address Downtown Burj Dubai right now. There are three Address Hotels dowtown - The Address Hotel Dubai Mall (newest, adjacent to the mall) , The Address Hotel Burj Dubai (recently built but second oldest Address Hotel, next door to the mall), and The Address Hotel Marina (oldest, near Marina). Be sure you know which hotel you are booking and clearly state the entire hotel name when giving directions to the cab driver.The Address Hotel Downtown Burj Dubai has a professional staff, rain showerhead and nice bath soaps, free wireless internet, free bottled water daily, in-room espresso machine with a variety of espresso flavors in disposable cups, large rooms, dark woods/marble/tile/glass/good lighting, complimentary turn down service with water (no chocolates), and has the greatest number of English TV channels of any other foreign hotel I've visited. Numerous well-heeled guests from all over the East and Western world stroll through with designer purses and pretty frocks under black abayas. The location is great - you can walk to the Dubai mall, Burj Dubai, and Dubai fountains. You can get a cab within seconds to go elsewhere. One perk about the lower floors is balconies, but not all rooms have them, so be sure to ask for a balcony room facing the fountains. There are two sections in the hotel - floors up to 12 use the house elevator and floors above 12 use the main elevator, so I recommend requesting a floor higher than 12 if you use the gym or spa. I stayed on the 10th floor, so to go to the spa and gym, I had to take the house elevator to the 12th floor and then walk up a flight. Otherwise, I had to walk through the lobby in gym clothes (you're underdressed in sneakers at this hotel). The staffed gym is nice - classes; free bottled water; machines have individual TVs with plugs for headsets or you can use their cheap, uncomfortable headsets; and oranges and apples in the lounge area. I received a great deep tissue massage in the spa. The spa relaxation area overlooks the Dubai fountains. There are oranges, tea, and juice in the relaxation area. The changing rooms have steam rooms and rain showerheads, there's a hairdryer but no showercaps or vanity items. The pool area is very nice, with a swim up pool bar that my collegues enjoyed. The pool bar area overlooks the fountains also. The service and amenities are 5 star, but you pay for it. I highly recommend this hotel.	
	A perfect stay	Wow ! We loved this hotel.I have been fortunate to visit Dubai many tmes and have stayed in many hotels, including the Burj Al Arab, and The Address has made it to my top 3. For a downtown hotel this would be my top choice.We had an executive suite with a fab view of the fountains and access to the club lounge, which was just,as others have said, superb. We ate breakfast in Fazaris because we preferred the range of choice in there but for everything else we used the lounge. Sarat and Apriel get a special mention from me but all of the staff were excellent. Club access did make the price more expensive but when you bear in mind that we dinner in there every night and had access to unlimite soft drinks, tea and coffee during the day, lunch if we wanted it, sandwiches, little quiches and cakes from 2.30pm till 5pm, and then dinner from 6pm till 8.30pm and alcoholic drinks from 6pm till 11pm it more than paid for itself.Aqua di Parma toiletries in the bathroom, great shower, fab bath and beautifully designed lay out.Suite was lovely, decor was soothing shades of brown and orange. I loved the fact that they had blackout curtains and comfy chairs on the balcony.The bed was sooooo comfy and the pillows were so good I have already written to see where they source them.There was a beautifull arrangement of fresh flowers delivered to the room just after we arrived and the smell of those flowers wafted across every time we opened the door of the room.The best thing about the executive suite was the 24 hour checkout and because we weren't leaving on our last day until 11.30pm in the evening we had none of the usual mad dash to checkout. we stayed by the pool all day, went back to the room to pack and had a quick snooze and then stayed in the club lounge until the car collected us at 11.30.We did venture up to Neos bar on the 63rd floor for a look at the view but weren't suitably dressed to mingle with the 'beautiful people' so didn't stay for a drink - any way no point paying for drinks when they were included in our club package.One minor niggle was the fact that the executive rooms only have king size beds, which would be great if you are travelling a deux. My friend was my sister so we shared a bed for the first time in 40 years. Having said that the beds are so big that we could have shared it with 3 others and not been squashed.One other less minor niggle was the fact that all of the lights and power points in the room are controlled by a switch at one side of the bed so it was impossible to leave the bed side light on - so if one person wanted to read for a bit then all of the lights stayed on. This also meant that my mobile phone couldn't charge over night. As I say a minor niggle, but if anyone from the Address reads this then it would be great to have bedside lights that operate independently to the main switch. : )Everything about our stay was excellent and I won't hesitate to return.	
