Nov 22 2009 	Outstanding Hotel...Can't wait to return!	Marhaba Y'all - I just returned from a week long stay at the Address Downtown and could not wait to come write the review. This hotel is outstanding! As this was a work trip, someone else handled my travel arrangements so all I knew was that we were at the Address but was not sure of much more than that (had no clue what class of room had been booked either). Once through customs at the airport, I stopped by the Address kiosk and they loaded me up in a BMW 750 for the 15 minute ride to the hotel. The driver was kind and had refreshments available for me in the car. I was thinking, so far so good! When we got to the hotel, I could not believe how beautiful it was. It, like much of the new construction in Dubai, is a striking, modern building, with beautful exterior lighting features and fountains everywhere. Check in was painless and the desk clerk accompanied me to the 7th floor Club Lounge to get me situated in my room. The room was nicely sized, with a super comfortable bed, full sofa, desk, and a nice 42-inch flat panel tv. The balcony was terrrific and had outstanding views overlooking the pool, and down towards the Dubai Fountain and the Burj Tower. Bathroom was super and had a great shower with all the usual upgraded complimentary bath products provided.Everyone of the hotel spoke as you passed by them in the halls and their English proficiency are all very acceptable. Ate in the restaurant by the pool every morning for their buffet which was amazing. Loved the fresh juice and all of the assortment each morning. Had dinner one night in the same restaurant and had the Lamb Tajine which was outstanding. Visited Neos on the 63rd floor mainly to see the view as it was slammed with all of the pretty people in the evening. Tried to go up around 5:45 pm one evening to snap some photos from up there and watch the sun set, but was disappointed to not be able to stay and see the sunset as they were not yet open. Did get a few quick photos but then had to depart. Seems like they are missing an opportunity for sunset drinks 63 floors up, but oh well. Minor.One note that needs to be made is that there are a number of ladies who ply their trade in the hotel bars. As I was solo, I was approached by several different ladies offering their services to help me pass the time. The hotel staff are all aware of it but there really isn't much they can do. No biggie, but be warned. It makes for an interesting story back home.In conclusion, this is an absolutely 5 star hotel with all of the ammenities you would expect and the customer service from the staff to back it up. I would defintely stay here again and HIGHLY recommend anyone else doing so. One slight complaint was that I I did not know about the extra benefits of the 7th floor club lounge, but it seems from other reviewers that there are some perks of which I should have been informed upon check in. Hate I missed those! I returned to the airport as I arrived, in the hotel's BMW. What a great ending to a great week!	
