Nov 4 2009	Cannot put into words how wonderful this hotel is!	We booked into a Club Premier Room at The Address Downtown Burj Dubai for our 4 night stopover on the way to Australia in September 2009, we did arrive at some silly hour in the morning (2.30am or something equally as ridiculous!), but as we were staying in a Club Room we had complimentary Ahlan Service at the Airport, so we were met at the top of the jetty, taken to an air conditioned lounge on a buggy, given drinks, biscuits and dates while our passports were stamped, we were then taken to collect our luggage and meet the driver from the hotel - amazing start! We were then transferred to the hotel in a 7 series BMW, the journey was only approx 15 minutes, but the driver gave us as much of a guided tour as he could at that time of the morning. Check in was seamless and within 20 minutes of arriving at the hotel we were in our room, with our luggage and all settled. Fabulous.The rooms are spacious, spotlessly clean and if you want anything (extra towels, extra pillows) you just picked up the phone and in no time they were with you. The beds are ridiculously comfortable and had Dubai not been such an amazing city with weather to die for I think I could have happily spent all of our stay in the bed. The housekeeping staff are brilliant - toiletries were regularly replaced and they gave us a giggle every day as my daughter had taken her teddy bear and flamingo with her - these were placed in a different position every day. Don't know if it was intentional, but it always put a smile on our faces.As we had booked a Club Room we had access to the Club Lounge where they serve 5 or so different presentations of food throughout the day. We ended up having nearly all our meals there as it was quiet and although there wasn't a huge selection, it was more than sufficient. Breakfast in the Club Lounge was amazing - a small cooked selection (Chicken &amp; Veal sausages, cooked tomatoes, Hash Browns etc...), pastries, cereals, freshly squeezed juices, we were also offered pancakes and eggs every morning too. The service in the Club Lounge is second to none, Marjolene and Apriel made our stay extra special, but all the staff in the Club Lounge must be mentioned as the service was out of this world! I think the service in the Club Lounge was the main reason we didn't try any of the other bars or restaurants in the hotel - we felt so welcome in the Lounge we didn't want to go anywhere else! Also, the view from the Terrace at the Club Lounge - well, words can't describe it. It overlooks the Burj Dubai and Dubai Fountain, so from 6pm onwards every night you have the most breathtaking view of the Dubai Fountain - it's just wonderful!The staff at the pool also need a mention in this review - they were so attentive it was unreal! The minute you chose your sunlounger they were over covering it with towels, creating a pillow with one for you, if you wanted to be in the shade they would move the lounger or the sun shades for you - you didn't have to lift a finger. The cold flannels that they came round with were lovely too, although they could have come round with them a little more often.The location of the hotel is fantastic, right beside Dubai Mall and just along from Souk Al Bahar, so perfect for shopaholics like me! To get to Dubai Mall and Souk Al Bahar from the hotel was wonderful - from the lobby you walk through the grounds, then you go down in the lift, out through a private entrance, across the walkway and you are in the mall. A five minute walk and you are in the biggest shopping mall in the world! If you are going to walk round the mall then take flat, comfortable shoes - I had 9 days in total in Dubai, most evenings I was in the mall and I still haven't made my way round the whole place!Everyone makes you feel so welcome at the hotel, all the staff say hello as they pass you in a corridor etc and it really did seem genuine, unlike some 5 star hotels. I have stayed in a lot of 5 star hotels, mainly in the UK and they really could learn a lot from The Address Downtown Dubai.We loved the hotel &amp; Dubai so much we changed our travel plans to include a week's stopover on the way back from Australia and can safely say our 2nd stay was even better than the first.If you are thinking of visiting Dubai and are not looking for a beach hotel then book a Club Room at The Address Downtown, it is worth every penny, you will relax from the moment you touch down at Dubai Airport as from then on everything is taken care of for you. I will be staying at The Address Downtown every time I go to Dubai, which will be at least 2 times a year and have already recommended the hotel to everyone I have spoken to.	
