Aug 9 2009 	Stunning hotel with amazing views	We have just returned form 8 nights at this exceptional hotel.I think we must have been staying at a different Address Hotel from the last few reviews!!We had an exceptional stay and with this being our 7th time in Dubai and having stayed at many of the other 5 star hotels, including Burj Al Arab, I would even say that The Address is probably our best choice yet.We had booked an Executive Suite which meant we were given the Ahlan service, which was excellent.We were met as soon as we entered the terminal building and were our passports were taken from us and the girl who met us took them to passport control while we waited in their own lounge, then transferred to the hotel by limousine were we were met and taken to our suite for check-in.When we reached our room, we were asked if I wanted to see the view we had. When he opened the doors to our balcony I could not believe what I was seeing. I never believed you could possibly get a balcony as big as this. He asked if I was happy with it.....happy????? I was ecstatic!!!We had a 4 poster sunbed with canopy, 2 sets of sunloungers, 2 chairs and small table, a dining table for 6 then a large decorative area with pebbles and shrubs and large urns. That was along along the front of the balcony with direct views on to Burj Dubai and The Fountains.Behind all that was a large seating area, another table for 4, a large garden area and a jacuzzi. I could definately get used to this, I thought!! We had access to the Club Lounge which was excellent and the staff there, especially Apriel, Sarat and Delee(not sure if this is the correct spelling). They made us so welcome from the very minute we stepped foot in the lounge. We didn't do breakfast in the lounge as there was much more choice in Fazaris, but we always had afternoon tea there and canapes etc. before we went out for dinner. You got complimentary tea. coffee, soft drinks all day and then from 6pm all drinks, including alcoholic drinks were complimentary until 11pm. You could sit on the terrace in the evening with your drinks and watch the Fountain display too.There was also free internet access on the 3 computers in the lounge. my only gripe is that when we were there, there were 3 children, who always seemed to be in the lounge on their own and they were always on the computers, even late at night. Several times I saw people coming in to go on them and after standing for a few minutes, they would walk away. I know their families had obviously booked club rooms but I feel it would be helpful if there was maybe another smaller Club Lounge for families. The lounge was always quiet and an excellent place just to relax.I totally disagree with the other reviewer about breakfast in Fazaris. The food was excellent, the choice was fantastic and staff were really nice too. The pool is such a lovely place to relax and the views are excellent. I also loved the &quot;rocking sunloungers&quot; they had in one pasrt of the pool. I could easily have just fell asleep. it was so soothing. All the staff at the pool were excellent too. One thing I did notice that the lifeguard who was on duty at the children's area was excellent with the children. He was with them constantly and didn't just sit in his stool watching them, but he actually interacted with them. all the children seemed to be having so much fun. Parents could sit back and relax knowing their children were in safe hands.Other than breakfast in Fazaris, we only ate in Hukama, which was excellent. We had no problems with the shower. unlike other guests and our room was always cleaned with fresh bedding everyday. The only small thing I noticed, which didn't bother us, but may bother others, was that at turn down service, our bed was never &quot;turned down&quot;. The room was tidied and water left at our bedside, but no &quot;small gifts&quot; like most of the other hotels leave at turndown and the bed left as it was. As I said, this did not bother us but it seemed strange that they didn't do this. Every hotel we have stayed in, in Dubai turned down your bed in the evening. We did have to phone them back to see when we were getting our iron delivered as I was still waiting for it in the late afternoon, when I had requested it before we went for breakfast. Honestly, there was nothing we could complain about here. We had the most amazing balcony with views to die for, excellent staff ,especially in the Club Lounge, the hotel was simply stunning and you only needed to walk down a flight of stairs and you were at The Dubai Mall. We had such an amazing time here, we are already making arrangements to return. If anyone is considering going to the Address, i would say go for it. Don't let some of the reviews put you off. We just loved it so much and definately would recommend a stay here.We definately will be returning to The Address again, and again, and again......	
Aug 7 2009 	Great hotel but not the best....	Our stay at The Address started off wonderful.... We booked a Premier room with Alhan service, and limo pickup at the Dubai airport. The staff at check-in were very nice and even upgraded us to an Executive Suite, which was a complete surprise to both of us. The room was very spacious with a large living room and bedroom. My wife and I both loved the ultra modern design of this hotel. I've stayed at many hotels in Dubai and, IMO, the Address has the best pool in Dubai. My wife and I spent most of the day relaxing poolside and then watching the fountain show from the pool bar. It was very relaxing....However, the hotel staff seem to lack attention to detail that I expect from this caliber of hotel There are 2 things I must have at any 5 star hotel in Dubai: Hot water and cold AC. The Address fails in both categories: - AC seemed to be broken in our room and several calls to front desk never seemed to get it fixed. Both my wife and I were forced to sleep without the bedding because the room was uncomfortably warm. Maybe that was why we were 'upgraded' to this room....- Major hot water issues in the morning.... The water will never stay at one constant temperature and will alternate between scorching hot and ice cold. In the afternoon/evening this doesn't seem to be an issue.- The hotel breakfast is overpriced and mediocre at best. The Grand Hyatt Dubai provides an outstanding breakfast for half the price.- Housekeeping skipped our room one day even though we were at the pool from 12 to 7pm. However, they were quick to send housekeeping up to clean the room.- Iron and ironing board was never removed after we requested it be removed twice. Its stayed in our room for the entire stay....- My wife and her sister were both asked for identification when entering the Neos bar on the 63rd floor even though they are both 24+ years old and staying in the hotel. We were forced to retrieve their passports from the rooms, which is about a 20 minute journey through 3 elevators. When we returned the staff who requested their identification was nowhere to be found and we were seated without any questions. This seemed ridiculous to me....I think this is an elegant hotel but I probably won't stay here again..... Other hotels in Dubai provide better value for the money. The housekeeping and room service staff just seem to lack attention to detail and there are still major hot water and AC issues that need to be resolved before I'd even return to this hotel.	
