Feb 19 2009 	Brilliant hotel in great location few minor moans though	We've just returned from a great five day break at this hotel. We were extremely happy with the accommodation, location and would happily go back. It is a very striking hotel with spacious rooms that are very comfortable and sumptuous.We were in a Grand Room and booked the hotel directly on their website which offered a 5 nights for 4 package. This package included transfers and breakfast. The transfer was very good as the hotel rep waited for us before immigration which helped speed us through some very long queues. We were in our room within 60 minutes of our plane landing which was a lovely start to our holiday.Our Grand Room was on the 12th floor which had panoramic views of the Burj, the lake and over The Palace Old Town. The bathroom was very good with separate shower cubicle but as previous reviews have mentioned the shower doesn't maintain a constant temperature.I was very happy with all aspects of this hotel but felt the staff needed more experience to offer a true five star service. There were also not enough concierge staff opening doors for arriving guests etc. and there did not appear to be any managers lurking in the background, helping to improve the level of service - the staff need more guidance to gain confidence.I'm posting lots of photos and hopefully these will demonstrate how striking the hotel is, it really is worth staying at, I've given a 5 star rating in this review for everything apart from the service. If you are considering this hotel then you definitely should try it.Positives were:The list is endless, as mentioned, this is a very stylish, sumptuous hotel in a brilliant location, we really had a fantastic stay.Breakfast at Farazi was very good and in a very calm, relaxed environment. The food stations would bring prepared food to you once you'd placed an order (no waiting here). They also had a fruit station that would juice whatever fruit you required.My nitpicking negatives were:- Shower, doesn't maintain temperature - we mentioned this on check out, they are aware of the problem- Door catches, the cupboards and wardrobes have those silly push to shut/close catches (do they ever work??)- Mini Bar/Coffee making area, unless the curtains are fully open flooding sunlight into the room this area is in complete darkness with no illumination - which annoyed me, design has to be functional not just look good. Which is nit picky, but I don't think an established luxurious hotel change would make these mistakes, and it's not very safe when you're handling a boiling kettle.	
Feb 18 2009 	Very Nice hotel - few minor issues to be improved	The Address is a very nice hotel with a great effort in the design that you can see in every detail. It is modern and sophisticate.It was supposed to be an international chain branded hotel, but then Emaar Properties decided to create their own &quot;Hotel Brand&quot; (they are going to open more The Address Hotel soon).I found the hotel very conveniently located as it is quite central if you want to move in Dubai and in a relatively acceptable distance from all other areas.Once construction around will be completed it will be definitively a prime location in Dubai. The pool is just amazing overlooking the Burj Dubai and the fountain square.Rooms are nice and well decorated (note, wifi does not work properly).Food is very nice.The staff is young and motivated, but i will say they miss some experience and this should be improved by the top management. A special mention to the SPA - me and my wife we are strong &quot;consumer&quot; of spa treatement, but trust me you will never find a better therapist then Mr. Erikson...that guy is just the best i have ever tried, by far.Yes, you can give The Address a try even if you are a demanding guest.	
Jan 23 2009 	Pleasant stay at The Address	My hunsand and I stayed in The Address from the 1st to the 10th January 2009. We booked the hotel directly with the hotel website and the price was very reasonable compared to the other 5 star hotels we have stayed in Dubai (5th trip).We booked a Grand room which gives lounge access. On arrival we were met at the airport and brought through passport control (fast queue) by a very pleasant staff member. Unfortunately Air France lost our bags so an hour later after staring at the baggage belt willing them to arrive we gave up and reported them. Arriving at your lovely 5 star hotel with only two toothbrushes, toothpaste, two Very Large t/shirts and a brush was not how we planned it but the hotel was happy to follow up on the baggage for us the following morning.Checkin was not great, the guy looked like he was not too interested in us and as it was 1230am in the morning at this point we were not in the best of form either. Got to our room which was very large and had two queen beds. Balcony had a lovely view of the Burj and the pool area below. The executive lounge is not the best one we have been in by a mile but it was functional. The staff seemed to be working very much without direction and for the first two days the lounge had a few people using it each morning and evening, however by the 3rd Jan it seemed to clear out and we were the only people in there most evenings having a drink which made it a bit boring with no atmosphere. The food was fine but they never refilled the units unless someone asked them to. Also the service of drinks is by the staff only so if they disappear for 30 minutes (which was prone to happen) you might be waiting a while for a drink..... The staff were helpful and efficient but no management appeared for the 9 days we were there. It was the first lounge however that served alchol until 11pm every evening and also provided 5 servings of food during the day so if you like the lounge area in a hotel, this is the one for you. We had breakfast there most mornings as it was quiet but the selection is much smaller than the main restuarant which serves everything you could want. Great Eggs Benedict!The pool area is large but if the hotel is full, it might be too small but it was fine while we stayed. Staff again are very helpful and offer you fresh fruit a couple times a day with cold towels once a day. Beds are comfortable and the water is a nice temperature.The gym was perfect for our needs on the 13th floor, only 4 treadmills but it was never too busy. The free weights and machines provided were top of the range so would definitely have no faults with it. Personal trainer can be booked also but the staff are helpful if you want to ask them any questions. The hotel is situated beside the Dubai Mall which intends to have 1200 shops when completed, there are about 400 open at present they said. It was a beautiful mall but it felt very empty and a lot of the bigger retailers have yet to open up so you may not get everything you want. We took a taxi to the Deira City Centre Mall and it was much better (only 25/30 AED) and for the first time there was no taxi queue when we went to leave at 10pm! Must be a sign of the times.The construction work going on around the hotel did not bother us at all, in fact even when you were lying by thte pool, you would be hard pressed to hear extensive noise. They were painting the floor of the new lake area while we were there and we would take a trip back just to see how it turned out. We had an Italian one evening in the new Gold/jewellery Souk mall beside the hotel and it was excellent (no drink license).I would recommend this hotel to you if you want a boutique style hotel with a good location. Rooms are good as are the facilities however as it is only 3 months old still it is having a few teething problems (leak in our shower took 5 days to get fixed and had to be reported 3 times). However we would still go back and stay there ourselves as price wise it is still not up at the other 5 star levels.Hope you enjoy your stay , (by the way our bags turned up 24 hours later than planned! )	
Jan 9 2009 	Neat Place and Location	A really cool hotel. I stayed one night for business and two nights for pleasure. Having stayed at a dozen 5-star hotels in Dubai, this is now my favorite. Upon checking in at 6:00 p.m. I was at first disapointed that my room was not ready. But, that was because they wanted to know if I would wait 20 minutes for a double upgrade to an executive suite. Sure!The room was huge, probably 80 sq. meters, with the longest balcony that I have seen. It had a bar, dining area, and two 50 inch LCD televisions -- not much selection on TV though. The four pools are beautiful. You feel like you can swim over the edge in the infinity pools but you are really five floors up. The pools roll into each other and one has a swim up bar.It would be even nicer if one of the jacazzui-looking pools actually had hot water. The water temperature was also a challenge in the room -- took some time before the shower warmed.The &quot;club&quot; lounge is fantastic -- serving three meals (breakfast is big but lunch and dinner small) and drinks -- free to those on club floors. Everyone was so nice and friendly. Though the pool attendants were a little overbearing, not leting me throw a towel upon a chair -- folding and refolding it everytime I went in the water. And always asking me if I wanted anything -- no just a swim and a little sun.I will stay at The Address again, and am also looking forward to visiting the new Address Dubai Mall that should open very soon. Though I may next visit the other sister hotel, The Palace, a few blocks away. The three hotels are close to the world's tallest building, Burj Dubai, and only a few steps from the world's largest -- Dubai Mall.	
Jan 8 2009 	Absolutely incredible hotel!	I reserved a room at &quot;The Address&quot; Downtown Burj Dubai for my partner and I by phone. I was immediately impressed by the helpfulness of the reservations staff members, who also provided assistance with obtaining a short-stay &quot;transit&quot; VISA for The United Arab Emirates and transfers from Dubai International airport. Upon arrival at the airport we were met before passport control by a rep from the hotel, who then accompanied us through the control, waited whilst we collected our luggage from the carousel and then escorted us to the waiting brand-new 7-series BMW limousine. Once comfortably seated in the limo the rep handed us cool refreshing hand-towels, bottles of mineral water and magazines before informing us that the journey would take approximately 30 minutes. I understand that the journey along the main road between the airport and the city can be a nightmare when it is busy; however with the sole exception of the road works near to the hotel there were no major delays and we arrived comfortably within 30 minutes.The Address Hotel had only been open for approximately 3 months when we arrived and is contained within a brand new skyscraper, which is centrally located next to The Burj Dubai construction site and The Dubai Mall. Although the hotel is primarily intended for business travelers due to its &quot;commercial&quot; surroundings I would still highly recommend it to leisure travelers, because if even for no other reason the fantastic views of the towering 800+ meter Burj Dubai have to be seen to be believed! Once we arrived at the hotel we were escorted to reception by the rep whilst the porters unloaded our luggage from the limo. Check-in took almost no time at all and within 3 minutes we were being escorted by the receptionist up to the tenth floor where our room was located.Our room was extremely large with a balcony and views overlooking the hotel swimming pool, gardens, The Burj Dubai and The Dubai Mall. In the far distance, by looking between two skyscrapers in the foreground, it was also possible to see the &quot;sail shaped&quot; Burj Al Arab 7-star hotel shimmering in the midday heat. Everything else within the room was exactly what you would expect in a 5-star luxury hotel with very modern dark-wood furniture, a large executive workstation, a 42 inch LCD TV and an i-pod docking station. The bathroom area contained a jacuzzi bathtub, double washbasins, separate WC and a shower cubicle complete with &quot;rain&quot; shower. Overall we were highly impressed with the quality of the hotel service, which was typified by the pool-side attendants who would rush over when you arrived and make up the sun-loungers with fresh towels. To be honest we were not at all bothered that we were not located on a beach because the hotel pool is just so good. Where else can you swim in such lovely clean, warm water while all the time looking up at The Burj Dubai?We only stayed in Dubai for 4 nights and we generally did not eat in the hotel because we preferred to go out and explore the city. We did have dinner in the main hotel dining room on one night, which was perfectly tasty although maybe just a little bit on the small side...we did not have a chance to eat at the gourmet Chinese restaurant. We also tried the hotel spa and found it to be extremely relaxing and we both agreed that probably these were the best massages we had ever had! Whilst exploring the hotel we were shown the gym by a member of staff, which looked extremely well equipped with the most state of the art machines although sadly we did not have a chance to make use of its facilities.Finally I will conclude my review of The Address hotel with one word....&quot;Neos&quot;. Neos is a very trendy hotel bar located right at the top of the skyscraper on the 63rd floor to which you must take two elevators. The first elevator takes you from the lobby to a &quot;sky lobby&quot; on 62nd floor that is decorated like the night sky, whilst a second smaller elevator takes you up to the bar from the sky lobby. Neos offers the most amazing views all over Dubai and it is particularly stunning at night. The only downside is that to have any chance of getting a table near to the windows so you can see the view properly, you need to make a reservation several days in advance because the bar is so popular with guests from surrounding hotels.	
Jan 8 2009	Location Ideal superb city hotel	We had 7 days and 6 nights at The Address most recently over the Christmas / New Year period and were quite impressed. Being familiar with many 5 star hotels in Dubai I chose this one particularly for its excellent location next to the new Dubai Mall andcentral position within reach of most of Dubai`s attractions. As mentioned in other reviews the decor, rooms, restaurants and appearance of hotel is excellent with a very nice gym and pool area. Overall service is good and staff always obliging yet not quite the standard of some other well established 5 star hotels in the city. My main complaint would have to be with the housekeeping service which was disappointing. Apart from making beds and cleaning the bathroom,no other cleaning was done in the room such as vacuuming nor dusting during the 6 days we were there. On 3 occasions turn down service was forgotten and I had to remind them about that. Faulty cupboard doors were also only attended to on our 3rd day there. The bathroom shower pressure was rather low and annoying at times and I think this is a problem often found with other guests as well.The Spa ,which is small and intimate does however lack a jucuzzi and sauna and the relaxation areas could only be used if a treatment was booked.We stayed in a grand room which was very nice , spacious and with lovely balcony view of the Burj Dubai.Overall I would still give this hotel a very good rating as it is still very new and would return in the future as I`m sure staff would be adequately trained and experienced by then.	
