Dec 31 2008 	Splendid Island in a Sea of Construction	At the time of this review, The Address Hotel has only been open for a couple of months. It is part of the massive “Downtown Burj Dubai” development, which also includes the Burj Dubai tower – now the tallest man-made structure on the planet – and the Dubai Mall. The hotel is impressive, both from the outside (especially at night) as well as inside. The décor in public areas and rooms is modern, but warm and very pleasant. The patio and pool areas are very inviting and quite spectacular. I stayed in a “Deluxe” room, which is the lowest category offered, but nevertheless quite spacious and well equipped as one would expect in this type of property.Breakfast at the main restaurant was very good, with a selection of Chinese, Indian, Arabic, and Western breakfast items. Dinner at the same restaurant was equally good, with a selection of Southeast Asian, Japanese, Indian, and Mediterranean dishes. The “Neos” bar on the 63th floor is worth a visit for spectacular views of the Downtown Burj Dubai all the way to Burj al Arab. I did not try the other restaurants on site; it would actually have been helpful to have a guide to restaurants at the hotel, as well as a guide to the area and Dubai Mall.The hotel staff was very friendly, courteous, and professional, although check in and out processes could still be a bit refined: e.g. my credit card was charged without explanation for 500 AED per day for “extras” in addition to the room rate; once checked in I waited 30 minutes for my one piece of luggage to appear, check out took an extra 10 minutes or so to process the breakfast charge an hour earlier.Overall, my stay at the hotel was a very pleasant experience, with the considerable construction around the hotel as the only drawback in the short-term. Once Dubai Mall is fully completed and occupied, and the remaining buildings and lakes in the area have been finished, this will be a nice base to stay and explore Dubai. Rates will probably go up too. If you go, consider a room with a balcony, and ask for a view of Burj Dubai.	
Dec 21 2008 	Nice Stay	We heard so much about the Address and wanted to try it out. It was a choice between Atlantis and the former hotel. The Address, it was. I can not find any fault to the hotel. It is brand new, very art decoish in a way. You can actually smell the &quot;newness&quot; in the air. We booked 2 rooms, one for my sister, and the other for my husband and I. The rooms are really nice, we were upgraded from a Premier one to a Grand room and the view of the pool and the Burj (tallest building) is beautiful. Our Balcony was quite huge and I just loved sitting there having my coffee and smoking away. It was my birthday, so as a compliment from the hotel, I got a delicious chocolate cake. Their service is really good, albeit it can get annoying at the restaurants when you have 2 or 3 people standing by waiting to serve you. We tried their food outlets. Their breakfast buffet had everything the heart desires. Dinner at their main restaurant, was so so. The Fois gras tasted really strange and was extremely hard, my lamb tagine, didnt taste as good as it looked. But whats really yummy was their Chinese restaurant. The food was scrumptuous, I highly recommend it. All in all a great experience. And if you dont want to eat at the hotel, theres a few other outlets in Souk Al Bahar, which you can walk to from the hotel. Its very close to their sister hotel, The Palace. The largest mall in dubai, the Dubai mall is also a walking distance. I enjoyed it, and Im sure others will enjoy it too...	
