Dec 2 2008 	Beautiful property but far from perfect	We stayed at this property for 3 nights. It is almost brand new, and everything certainly looks that way. High end LCD screen, comfortable bed, great bathroom facilities, etc.Check in wasn't great. The standard check-in time was 3pm. We arrived at 2.45pm and were told &quot;your room is not ready because you arrived early at 2.45pm&quot;. After getting into the room, we found the remote for the iPod docking station does not have a battery. It took them SEVEN hours and five calls to give us a battery. The docking station is absolutely useless without the remote as all control functions are available only via the remote.It is nice they come to set your room up for the evening, however they only left us one bottle of water and one pair of slippers when there were 2 guests in the room.We got chocolates for the first night, but nothing for the 2nd and last night. Shower temp is a huge issue to be resolved. When the water is warm, everything is fantastic, however every 2-3 minutes the water just turns icy cold, so be aware. We have tried taking shower at different times of a day, but it seems to make no difference.The Chinese restaurant is always fully booked, so if you want to secure a table, book early.The pool is one of the best features of this hotel. It's beautifully designed, and has unobstructed view of the Burj Dubai (tallest tower of the world at the moment).The quality of food from orders placed at room service was very good, and it's a good thing that they don't charge you anything extra for ordering food at 2am in the morning. However in one morning the poached eggs arrived &quot;warm&quot; to say at best, when we were expecting some hot breakfast.The worst experience came on the day of our check out. I requested a 1pm check out instead of 12pm as we wanted to go for a swim in the morning. It was pleasantly agreed by the reception. However they disabled my room key at noon, and we couldn't go back to my room after the pool, while we were wet and cold. There was no apoligies made and it took them 15 minutes to figure out what the problem is before letting us back into the room.The bar on the 63rd floor is worth a visit, although the night we visited they wanted $100 AED &quot;cover charge&quot; just to get up there.Overall this hotel is stunning to look at inside out, however you should think about it twice before making the booking if you expect a true 5 star experience.	
